.TH "HTMLTextAreaElement.defaultValue" "JS" "September 11, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLTextAreaElement.defaultValue \- HTMLTextAreaElement: defaultValue
property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]defaultValue\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLTextAreaElement\f[R] interface represents the default text
content of this text area.
Getting and setting this value is equivalent to getting and setting
\f[CR]textContent\f[R] on the \f[CR]<textarea>\f[R].
.SH VALUE
A string.
.SH EXAMPLES
In the example below, the \f[CR]defaultValue\f[R] still returns the
value originally written in the HTML.
If a default value is set, either via HTML or the
\f[CR]defaultValue\f[R] property, user input will update the
\f[CR]value\f[R] but will not overwrite the \f[CR]defaultValue\f[R].
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] textareaElement = document.getElementById(\[dq]comment\[dq]);
console.log(textArea.defaultValue);
textArea.defaultValue = \[dq]This is the default text now!\[dq];
.EE
